5s5.title: Operations in Set theory
5s5.text:
An operation in [3jz set] theory is a [-3jy] of two sets, that returns a set.

Common set operations include [5s8 Union ($\cup$)], [5sb Intersection ($\cap$)], [5sc Relative complement ($\setminus$)], and [3xb Cartesian product ($\times$)].

![illustrations of the output of four basic set operations](https://imgh.us/basic_set_operations_1.svg)
